<item>
            <title>[LU-8688] All Lustre test suites should run/PASS with separate MDS and MGS</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8688</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Since separate MDS and MGS is a common and recommended Lustre set-up, full test group and patch testing should be run against this Lustre configuration. We can request a separate MDT and MGT (both on the same node/VM) for autotesting by using &#8216;Test-Parameters: combinedmdsmgs=false&#8217; in a patch commit message and, thus, we are able to test separate targets (only separate targets and not separate nodes). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The purpose of this ticket is to track the various efforts/tickets that are working to get the Lustre test suites running on separate MDS and MGS. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
